Fetching: Macro action using both search and deliver macros, all packaged under one action to help keep better track of
destinations

how will search and deliver macros work?

Search: only called when memory isn't aware of place to collect, if colonist already knows where item could be
move micro is queued.
Deliver: makes delivery and takes it back, theoretically more straightforward


Fetch:

parameters

Tile origin: where the search as assigned, useful to construct deliveries back, why a fetch macro was made to avoid juggling destinations around the generic colonist actions, containing all logic in fetch class

Tile deliverydest (optional): if the colonist is supposed to take the item to somewhere other than where the search was assigned, this is saved

first 2 parameters are important for making it easier to construct the delivery once items are found